PESTE DES PETITS RUMINANTS - CHINA (10): SHEEP, GOAT, SPREAD, OIE
*****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 22 Apr 2014
Source: OIE, WAHID Weekly Disease Information 27 (17) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=15093


Information received on 22 Apr 2014 from Dr Zhang Zhongqui, Director General, China Animal Disease Control Centre, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing, China (People's Rep. of).

Summary:
15 new outbreaks

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 15, in 5 provinces: Jilin (1), Heilomgjiang (4), Shanxi (3), Shaanxi (1) and Yunnan (6).
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep & goats / not available / 2180 / 1033 / 5367 / 0

Outbreak statistics
Apparent case fatality rate: 47.39 percent

Measures applied: Stamping out, Quarantine, Movement control inside the country, Screening, Zoning, Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s), Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), Dipping/Spraying, No treatment of affected animals

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The total number of PPR outbreaks since the start (on 5 Dec 2013) of the current epizootic in China is 150, and the epizootic is termed as "continuing."

For details on each of the 15 new outbreaks, including morbidity, mortality and culling figures, and for their respective locations in an interactive map, please refer to the source URL.

Information on the numbers of vaccinated animals in each of the affected provinces will be welcomed. Is preventive vaccination applied in all of China's provinces?

PPR is not zoonotic. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2422764,155.]
